 to explain the facts of development as well as the learnability problem, reporting on work in the mainstream formalist framework but also considering the results of alternative approaches. Covering a wide range of perspectives in the modern study of syntactic development, this book is an invaluable reference for specialists in the field of language acquisition and provides an excellent introduction to the acquisition of syntax for students and researchers in psychology, linguistics, and cognitive science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish language. 0aGrammar, Comparative and general. 0aLanguage acquisition. 0aLanguage and languages. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  alinguistics reference, broad critical survey, research literature, child language development, empirical issues, theoretical, syntax of english, developmental data, syntactic phenomena, anaphora, passives, relative clauses, inversion, wh-questions, embedded, subject drop, word order, learnability problem, mainstream formalist framework, alternative approaches, acquisition, cognitive science, psychology, utterances, constraints on coreference.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226620787423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226620787/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles